  "text_content": "Lore Olympus is a work of pure fiction inspired by Greco-Roman mythology. The events and characters portrayed in Lore Olympus are not intended to be canonically consistent with the original poems, plays, and hymns of the ancient world. Lore Olympus is not designed to be cited as a scholarly source on mythology except in the analysis of literature, media, the arts, the humanities, etc.\n\n\nIf you are interested in mythology, here is a list of some works of antiquity:\n\n- The Homeric Hymns\n- Homer, Odyssey\n- Hesiod, Theogony\n- Hesiod, Works and Days\n- Nonnus, Dionysiaca\n- Ovid, Metamorphoses\n\nEnquire at your local library for more recommendations.",
